        <div style="padding-top:260px; text-align:center; margin-right:90px; margin-left:90px;  line-height:1.9; font-size:14px;" >
            <span ><Strong><u>AGREEMENT FOR SALE OF FLAT</u></Strong></span>
        </div>
        <div style="text-align:center; margin-right:90px; margin-left:90px;  line-height:1.8; font-size:13px;">
            
            
            <p style="text-align:justify; font-size:14px">
                THIS <strong>AGREEMENT FOR SALE OF FLAT</strong> ENTERED INTO AT CHENNAI ON this the <span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:60px; padding:0px; margin:0;line-height:1"></span> day of <span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:60px; padding:0px; margin:0;line-height:1"></span>, 2024.
            </p>
            <p style="padding-top:10px; padding-bottom:10px; font-size:14px">
                <strong>BY</strong> 
            </p>
            <p style="text-align:justify; font-size:14px">
                <strong> M/s. JAIN HOUSING LLP, (PAN: AAOFJ0016H)</strong> a Limited Liability Partnership firm, registered under the Limited Liability Partnership Act, 2008, having its registered office at No.98/99, Habibullah Road, T. Nagar, Chennai – 600017, represented by its Authorized signatory <strong> Mr. CHENARAM SENI </strong>(AADHAAR:<strong> 4318 8506 6098</strong>), S/o. Mr. Ridharamji, aged about 52 years, (duly authorized vide Board Resolution dated 04-03-2025) residing at No.167A/F10, Jains Eiffel Garden, Arcot Road, Vadapalani, Chennai- 600 026 hereinafter referred to as the<strong> “VENDOR/PROMOTER”</strong> (which expression shall unless repugnant to the context or meaning there of be deemed to mean and include his/her heirs, executors, administrators, successors-in-interest and permitted assignees).
                
            </p>
            <p style="padding-top:10px; padding-bottom:10px; font-size:14px">
                <strong>TO AND IN FAVOUR OF</strong>
            </p>
            <p style="text-align:justify; font-size:14px">
                Mr./Mrs. <span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:80px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span>, (Aadhar No. <span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:60px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span>) (PAN <span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:60px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span>) son/ daughter/ wife of <span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:60px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span>aged about&nbsp;<span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:30px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span> years, residing at <span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:60px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span>  here in after called the<strong> “ALLOTTEE/PURCHASER”</strong> (which expression shall unless repugnant to the context or meaning there of be deemed to mean and include his/her heirs, executors, administrators, successors-in-interest and permitted assignees).
                
            </p>
            <div style="page-break-after: always"></div>
            
            <p style="text-align:justify; font-size:14px">
                <strong>WHERE AS </strong>the Vendor/Promoter is the absolute owner of the property measuring an extent of 2 Acres [8040 Sq. mt. as per Patta]   in Old S.No. 410, New S.No. 410/1A1A presently T.S. No.3, Ward- A, Block- 13, situated at Nookampalayam Link Road, Semmancherry Village, (formerly Ganapathy Syndicate Colony, Tambaram Taluk), Sholinganallur Taluk, Chennai District, more fully described in the Schedule “A” hereunder, having purchased the same from M/s. SMT Property Developers Pvt. Ltd., vide Sale Deed dated 27.02.2023 registered as Doc. No. 3724/2023 in the office of the Sub Registrar at Neelankarai
                
            </p>   
            
            
            <p style="text-align:justify; font-size:14px; padding-top:20px">
                <strong>WHERE AS</strong> the Vendor /Promoter has set apart an extent of 426.00 Sq.mt. or 4585.46 Sq.ft. in Old S.No. 410, New S.No. 410/1A1A presently T.S. No.3, Ward- A, Block- 13, to be gifted towards establishment of a Substation to the Tamil Nadu Electricity Board (TNEB).
                
            </p>
            
            
            <p style="text-align:justify; font-size:14px; padding-top:20px">
                <strong>WHERE AS</strong> the Vendor after deducting an extent of 426.00 Sq.mt. or 4585.46 Sq.ft. in Old S.No. 410, New S.No. 410/1A1A presently T.S. No.3, Ward- A, Block- 13, the vendor became vested with an extent of 7614 Sq.mt or 81957.54 Sq.ft. comprised in Old S.No. 410, New S.No. 410/1A1A presently T.S. No.3, Ward- A, Block- 13, situated at Nookampalayam Link Road,Semmancherry  Village, (formerly Ganapathy Syndicate Colony, Tambaram Taluk), Sholinganallur Taluk, Chennai District, more fully described in the Schedule “B” hereunder.
            </p>
            <p style=""></p>
            <p style="text-align:justify; font-size:14px; padding-top:20px">
                <strong>WHERE AS</strong> the Vendor/Promoter had obtained requisite sanctions, authorizations, consents, no objections, permissions and approvals from the appropriate authorities for construction and development of the Project vide <strong>Planning Permit No.15617 PP/HRB/09/2024/A to G dated 05/07/2024 and Building Permit No. CEBA/WDCN15/00431/2024 dated</strong> 31/07/2024 duly issued by Greater Chennai Corporation/Local-body;
                
            </p>
            <p style="text-align:justify; font-size:14px; padding-top:20px">
                <strong>WHERE AS</strong> the Vendor/ Promoter has registered the project under the provisions of the Act with <strong>Real Estate Regulatory Authority at Chennai on 29.10.2024 under Registration No. TN/29/Building/0514/2024</strong>
                
            </p>
            <div style="page-break-after:always;"></div>
            <p style="text-align:justify; font-size:14px; padding-top:30px">
                <strong> THAT</strong> the Vendor/Promoter is in absolute possession and enjoyment of the above said land more fully described in Schedule A hereunder.
                
            </p>
            <p style="text-align:justify; font-size:14px; padding-top:20px">
                <strong>WHERE AS</strong> the Vendor/Promoter have proposed to construct Residential buildings in the schedule "B" property hereunder and obtained necessary approval for the same from Competent Authorities.
                
            </p>
            <p style="text-align:justify; padding-top:20px">
                <strong>WHERE AS</strong> the <strong>Allottee/Purchaser</strong> has already scrutinized / verified all sanctions, authorizations, consents, no objections, permissions and approvals issued by the appropriate authorities and is satisfied with the title and statutory compliance with regards to the Project; and
                
            </p>
            <p style="text-align:justify; padding-top:20px">
                
                <strong>WHERE AS</strong>the Allottee/Purchaser is interested in purchasing one residential Flat No<span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:20px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span> having super built up area of <span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:20px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span>Sq.ft of the building and corresponding common rights in stair case, common veranda other common facilities and amenities and approached the Vendors/ Promoter. The Vendors/Promoter have agreed to sell the said apartment  with<span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:20px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span> sq.ft undivided rights out of Schedule “B” property more fully described in Schedule “C” hereunder and the Allottee/Purchaser has agreed to purchase the same for a total sale consideration of Rs.<span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:30px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span> /- (Rupees <span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:80px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span> only).
                
            </p>
            <p style="text-align:justify; padding-top:20px">
                <strong>WHERE AS</strong> the Vendor/Promoter have assured the Allottee/Purchaser that Schedule “C” property is completely free from mortgage, charge, lease, lien, attachment by court and such other authorities, suit, arrears of taxes, arrears of electricity and water charges and other dues and other encumbrances and impediments whatsoever. 
            </p>
            <p style="text-align:justify; padding-top:20px">
                <strong>WHERE AS</strong> the Allottee/Purchaser having inspected all the documents of title of the property in the possession of the Vendor/Promoter as well as the plans, specifications and all other documents relating to the property and the building project and having been satisfied on the validity of the title and feasibility of the project, the Allottee/Purchaser has come forward to purchase the flat /apartment more particularly mentioned in Schedule “C” hereunder written.
            </p>
          
            <p style="text-align:justify; padding-top:20px">
                WHERE AS the Vendor/Promoter offered to sell the Flat bearing No.<span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:20px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span>, <span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:20px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span> Floor, measuring <span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:20px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span> Sq.ft. super built up area together with <span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:20px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span> Sq.ft. undivided share out of Schedule B property and <span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; min-width:40px; padding:0; margin:0;"></span> No. of Covered/Open/Combined Car Park, more fully described in Schedule “C” to the Allottee/Purchaser for a consideration of Rs<span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:30px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span>/- (Rupees<span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:80px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span> only) free of all encumbrances.
            </p>
            
            <p style="text-align:justify; padding-top:20px">
                <strong>WHERE AS</strong> the Allottee/Purchaser on the faith of the representation of the Vendors/Promoter that the Vendors/Promoter have an absolute and indefeasible title to the Schedule “A” land and the Vendor/Promoter is entitled to develop the Schedule “B” property, agrees to purchase the flat more fully described in Schedule “C” and hereinafter referred to as the property for the said consideration of Rs<span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:30px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span> (Rupees <span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:80px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span>only) free of all encumbrances on the following terms and consideration.
            </p>
            <p style="text-align:justify; padding-top:20px">
                Now, in consideration of the premises here in before recited and further consideration of the benefits, rights, restrictions and obligations respectively accruing to and undertaken by the parties here to, this agreement witnessed as follows:
            </p>
            <p style="text-align:justify; padding-top:20px">
                <strong>WHERE AS</strong> the Parties have decided to reduce the terms and conditions mutually agreed upon into writing through these presents.
            </p>
            <p style="text-align:justify; padding-top:20px">
                <strong><u>NOW THEREFORE THIS AGREEMENT WITNESSETH AS FOLLOWS:</u></strong>
            </p>
            <p style="text-align:justify; padding-top:10px">
                The Vendor/Promoter and the Allottee/Purchaser mutually agree and covenant as follows:
            </p>
            <p style="padding-top:20px; text-align:justify;">
                1. <span style="padding-left: 30px"><strong><u>ALLOTMENT:</u></strong></span>
            </p>
            <p style="text-align:justify; padding-top:10px; margin-top:-20px">
                The Vendor/Promoter hereby agrees to sell/construct &amp; allot and deliver the Apartment, as per the specifications mentioned in the Annexure 1 hereunder, to the Allottee/Purchaser at the cost of the Allottee/Purchaser.
                
            </p>
            <p style="padding-top:20px; text-align:justify;">
                2.<span style="padding-left: 30px; "><strong><u>SALE CONSIDERATION AND OTHER RELATED PAYMENTS:</u></strong></span>
            </p>
           
            <table>
                <tr>
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;" >a)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify; ">The Sale Consideration for the Schedule “C” mentioned apartment based on the carpet area is Rs.<span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:30px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span>/-(Rupees<span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:80px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span> only). The Sale Consideration includes the following</td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-left:30px; padding-top:15px; padding-bottom:15px">
                    <table width="100%" style="border-collapse:collapse; border:1px solid line; ">
                        <tr>
                            <td width="40%" style="padding-left:20px; padding-right:10px; padding-top:5px; padding-top:5px; border:.7px solid #000">
                                Apartment No.<span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:20px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span>, in <span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:20px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span> Floor, measuring <span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:20px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span> Sq.ft. of Carpet Area, Total Area of <span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:20px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span> Sq.ft (Comprising of carpet area + Wall Thickness &amp; Balcony  and   + proportionate share in common areas) and the cost of undivided share of land
                            </td>
                            <td width="40%" style="border:.7px solid #000">Amount</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            
                            <td style="border:.7px solid #000">Sale Consideration</td>
                            <td style="border:.7px solid #000">Rs.</td>
                            
                        </tr>
                        
                    </table>
                </div>
            </table>
            <table>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%"></td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">The Sale consideration above includes the booking amount paid by the Allotte/Purchaser to the Vendor/Promoter towards the Apartment; The Sale Consideration mentioned above is a consolidated cost which is final and supersedes all calculations/estimates shared to the Allottee[s]/Purchaser[s]. The aforesaid Sale Consideration is payable as per the milestones set out in Schedule D here under (excluding GST).</td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px;"></div>
                
                
                <tr>
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;" >b)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">The sale consideration above is exclusive of Taxes payable to the Government as per the norms/rules which are prevailing at present. In case of any change/modification in the quantum of GST or introduction of any new/additional tax before handing over possession, the Allottee/Purchaser undertakes to pay the same in addition to the above said construction cost before handing over possession of Schedule “C” property.  Provided that in case there is any change / modification in the existing taxes and/or introduction of any other new taxes in future which is subsequent to the handing over possession of Schedule “C” property, the Allottee/Purchaser undertakes to pay the same without any objection. 
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px;"></div>
                
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">c)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">The Vendor/Promoter shall not be obliged to send a separate intimation regarding the stage completion and demand of any payment.  The delay in payment shall attract interest @ 18 % p.a. </td>
                </tr>
                
                <div style="padding-top:20px;"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">d)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">The Allottee/Purchaser shall contribute with other Purchasers of divided/undivided share/s in the said Land, for any levy for betterment or development of the land that may be levied by the Corporation, Government or any other Public or Town Planning Authority and in this regard on and from this day, the Allottee/Purchaser shall bear and pay the taxes that may be levied on the said land in proportion to his/her share as set out in Schedule ‘C’ here under.
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px;"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">e)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">The Allottee/Purchaser shall bear and pay the stamp duty, registration fee, documentation and legal charges in respect of this Agreement and/or on any other document that may be called for or levied by the Government, Stamp or Registration Authorities or Tax Authorities as applicable at the time of registration. Provided that in the event of any increase or enhancement/introduction of a new levy in future / post registration, the same shall also be borne and paid by the Allottee/Purchaser.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px;"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">f)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">The Allottee/Purchaser shall bear, contribute and pay in proportion to his/her share for all and any deposits, expenses, and levies for the purpose of securing electricity, water(if applicable for the locality ) and sewage connections and also for securing the assessment for property tax and vacant land tax by the Corporation now levied and that may be levied in future.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px;"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">g)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">The Sale Consideration is escalation-free, save and except increases, which the Allottee/Purchaser here by agrees to pay, due to any additional work requested by the Allottee/Purchaser, increase on account of development and other charges payable to the competent authority and/or any other increase in charges, which may be levied or imposed by the competent authority on the Project from time to time. It is also agreed that owing to Mivan Structure any alteration or changes in the specifications / plan shall not be entertained under any circumstances. 
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px;"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">h)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">The Vendor/Promoter undertakes and agrees that while raising a demand on the Allottee/Purchaser for increase in development charges, cost/charges imposed by the competent authorities, the Vendor/Promoter shall quote the said notification/order/rule/regulation to that effect along with the demand letter being issued to the Allottee/Purchaser.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px;"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">i)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">The Allottee/Purchaser) shall make the payment as per the payment plan set out in Schedule “D” (“Payment Plan”). The Allottee/Purchaser authorizes the Vendor/Promoter to adjust/appropriate all payments made by him/her under any head(s) of dues against lawful outstanding, if any, in his/her name as the Vendor/Promoter may in its sole discretion deem fit and the Allottee/Purchaser undertakes not to object/demand/direct the Vendor/Promoter to adjust this payment in any manner.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px;"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">j)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">The Allottee/Purchaser agrees to pay towards maintenance charges Rs.3.5/- per sq.ft. per month + Applicable GST charges per month for the period of 36 Months to the Vendor/Promoter before taking over possession of the flat towards maintaining the amenities and common amenities for the entire project. Such maintenance charges shall become applicable from the date of intimation regarding the readiness of Schedule “C” property with basic occupational amenities such as  drainage, electricity and lift facilities. The scope of maintenance services is more clearly described in the Annexure 2 herein.  No additional requests shall be entertained other than the scope. However, if any additional works done over and above the scope mentioned in Annexure 2, the expenses shall be met with by the Promoter from and out of the Corpus fund. The Allottee agrees that the maintenance shall be automatically stand renewed and extended for a further period of 36 months from the date of expiration of initial 36 months subject to the terms as detailed in clause 6(d) herein below.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px;"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">k)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">The Allottee/Purchaser shall also, before handing over of possession of Schedule “C” mentioned apartment, pay to the Vendor/Promoters sum of Rs.29,500/- (Twenty Nine Thousand Five Hundred  Only) as Owner’s contribution towards “Corpus Fund”. The Corpus Fund will be utilized towards major repairs, payment of AMCS for various equipment / infrastructures provided thereof (STP/Lift/DG etc), diesel consumption for DGs, fused bulb / electrical fixture replacements, STP O &amp; M cost &amp; electricity charges, landscaping improvements, and for any capital expenditure such as purchase of additional motors, DGS and any other up-gradation or enhancement activities done to the project or enhancements / improvements done towards the maintenance services over and above the scope envisaged in Annexure 2 hereunder and every other up-gradation/repair works done towards up- keeping the common amenities during Vendor/Promoter’s maintenance tenure.  The Vendor/Promoter, after attaining 85% of sales of the entire project, shall transfer the above corpus fund to the Flat Owners Association/Society without interest, after adjusting all the expenditure incurred thereof. The OWNERS or the Owner’s Association/Society shall have no right or authority to claim the refund/transfer of the corpus fund from the Developer before attaining 85% of sales of the entire project as set out above. The contribution towards Corpus Fund is collected to ensure funds availability for the above mentioned purposes.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px;"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">l)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">It is made clear that the cost incurred for any additional specification which are provided in the Schedule “C” apartment, but are not forming Part of the Annexure – 1 herein shall be claimed by the VENDOR/PROMOTER from the ALLOTTEE/PURCHASER at any point of time even after handing over possession of Schedule ”C” property.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                
            </table>
            <p style="padding-top:20px; text-align:justify;">
                3.<span style="padding-left: 30px"><strong><u>MODE OF PAYMENT:</u></strong></span>
            </p>
            
            
            
            <table>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(a)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/Purchaser has paid a sum of <strong>Rs.</strong><span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:40px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span>/-(<strong>Rupees</strong><span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:80px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span><strong>only</strong>), to the Vendor/Promoter vide ChequeNo.<span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:20px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span> dated<span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:20px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span> drawn on <span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:20px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span>Bank,<span style="display:inline-block; border-bottom:.7px solid #000; width:40px; padding:0px; margin:0;"></span>Branch Chennai, as booking amount at the time of allotment of the Apartment;
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(b)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/Purchaser shall pay the balance consideration amount as per the schedule of payments detailed in the SCHEDULE– D here under;  
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(c)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/Purchaser hereby undertake/s and assure/s that based on the stage intimation letter issued/ to be issued by the Vendor/Promoter to the Allottee, the above payments shall be made by the Allottee within due date as time for payment of the above said sums being the essence of the contract and the Allottee is fully informed by the Vendor/Promoter that any default in payment of the above said amount would affect the completion of the Project; All the delayed payment would attract interest @ 18% p.a. 
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(d)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Venor/Promoter further clarified to the Allottee/Purchaser that the Allottee/Purchaser  shall be solely responsible for availing housing loan from any Bank/Financial Institution towards the purchase of the Schedule “C” property and if there is any delay of payment out of such funding then the Allottee/Purchaser shall be responsible for the same.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(e)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        All payments shall be made by Cheque/s or Demand Draft/s or through RTGS.  The date of credit of the amount into the account of the Vendor/Promoter will be considered as the date of payment made by the Allottee/Purchaser and the delayed payment charges will become payable from the due date;
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(f)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        In the event that the Allottee[s] / Purchaser or his/her banker makes payment through RTGS/NEFT or any other mode of electronic fund transfer, or through any other bank account operated by the co-allottee or any other account, the Allottee[s]/Purchaser[s] shall intimate/keep intimated the builder/promoter of such payments within 3 working days of such payment either through a written / electronic mail communication, so as to enable to Builder / Promoter to credit such payments to their respective account.  Failing to do so, the Allottee[s]/Purchaser[s] understand that the reconciliation of their respective ledger/account shall be hampered drastically and would cause delay in the process of handing over.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(g)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/Purchaser shall not delay, withhold or postpone the payments due as mentioned in SCHEDULE-“D”, on whatever reason and in that event, Allottee/Purchaser shall be responsible for any consequential sufferance or damages and they shall adhere to clause5(a)(1) mentioned herein.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(h)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/Purchaser, if resident outside India, shall be solely responsible for complying with the necessary formalities as laid down in Foreign Exchange Management Act, 1999, Reserve Bank of India Act and Rules and Regulations made there under or any statutory amendment(s) modification(s) made thereof and all other applicable  laws  including  that of remittance of payment acquisition/sale/transfer of immovable properties in India etc. and provide the Vendor/Promoter with such permission, approvals which would enable the Vendor/Promoter to fulfill its obligations under  this Agreement. Any refund, transfer of security, if provided in terms of the Agreement shall be  made in accordance with the provisions of Foreign Exchange Management Act, 1999 or statutory enactments or amendments thereof and the Rules and Regulations of the Reserve Bank of India or any other applicable law. The Allottee/Purchaser understands and agrees that in the event of any failure on his/her part to comply with the applicable guidelines issued by the Reserve Bank of India; he/she shall be liable for any action under the Foreign Exchange Management Act, 1999 or other laws as applicable, as amended from time to time. The Vendor/Promoter accepts no responsibility in this regard. The Allottee/Purchaser shall keep the Vendor/Promoter fully indemnified and harmless in this regard. Whenever there is any change in the residential status of the Allottee/Purchaser subsequent to the signing of this Agreement, it shall be the sole responsibility of the Allottee/Purchaser to intimate the same in writing to the Vendor/Promoter immediately and comply with necessary formalities if any under the applicable laws. The Vendor/Promoter shall not be responsible towards any third party making payment/remittances on behalf of any Allottee/Purchaser and such third party shall not have any right in the application/allotment of the said apartment applied for herein in any way and the Vendor/Promoter shall be issuing the payment receipts in favor of the Allottee/purchaser only.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(i)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/Purchaser shall be entitled to possession or even seek possession of the property described in Schedule “C” hereunder ONLY upon completion of all payments due and payable to the Vendor/Promoter and subject to the condition mentioned in clause 3(j) below. Further, the Allottee/Purchaser shall not be entitled to either by himself/herself or through any agent/ workers, carry out any interior or furnishing work in the Apartment described  in  SCHEDULE “C”, until all payments are completed and possession is handed over to the Allottee/Purchaser.  
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(j)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/Purchaser agrees and shall pay all the amount dues (100%) as per this agreement before he/she could claim or become entitled to delivery of possession of the Apartment as well as delivery of the Original of this Agreement and the registration of Sale Deed. After making the entire payment as stipulated in this Agreement, the Allottee/Purchaser shall duly make an application to the VENDOR/PROMOTER for issuance of No Due Certificate along with other documents such as Affidavit, Customer Satisfaction Report etc., in the form and manner prescribed by the Vendor/Promoter within 15 days of which, the VENDOR/PROMOTER shall issue No Due Certificate to the Allottee/Purchaser.  The possession of Schedule “C” mentioned property shall be delivered to the Allottee/Purchaser within 15 days from the date of issuance of No Due Certificate. 
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
            </table>
            <p style="padding-top:20px; text-align:justify;">
                4.<span style="padding-left: 30px"><strong><u>PERIOD  OF COMPLETION  AND HANDING OVER OF POSSESSION:</u></strong></span>
            </p>
            <table>
                
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">a)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Vendor/Promoter shall endeavor to complete the construction of the Apartment in the project within _________with grace period of 6 months from the date of this Agreement. The Vendor/Promoter agrees and understands that timely delivery of possession of the Apartment is the essence of the Agreement. The Vendor/Promoter, based on the approved plans and specifications, assures to hand over possession of the Apartment as committed, unless there is delay or failure due to war, flood, drought, fire, cyclone, earthquake, epidemic/pandemic/lockdown or any other calamity caused by nature affecting the regular development of the real estate project (“Force Majeure”). If, however, the completion of the Project and/or delivery of the apartment is delayed due to the Force Majeure conditions and/or delay in securing completion certificate and amenities like water, electricity, etc., from the Concerned Authorities including getting the Apartments assessed to tax notwithstanding the completion of the construction of the apartment,  then the Allottee/Purchaser agrees that the Vendor/Promoter shall be entitled to the extension of time for delivery of possession of the Apartment, provided that such conditions are not of a nature, which make it impossible for the contract to be implemented. The Allottee/Purchaser agrees and confirms that, in the event it becomes impossible for the Vendor/Promoter to implement the project due to Force Majeure conditions, then this allotment shall stand terminated and the Vendor/Promoter shall refund to the Allottee/Purchaser the entire amount received by the Vendor/Promoter from the allotment within (60) days from that date of determination of impossibility of performance. After refund of the money paid by the Allottee/Purchaser, Allottee/Purchaser agrees that he/ she shall not have any rights, claims etc. against the Vendor/Promoter and that the Vendor/Promoter shall be released and discharged from all its obligations and liabilities under this Agreement. In event of VENDOR/PROMOTER undertakes any alteration / change / additional / extra work,  then the VENDOR/PROMOTER shall have unfettered right to schedule / take up such work at any point of time as they deem fit and shall be entitled to delay/defer the handing over schedule of Schedule “C” property.  In such an event, the said delay shall not be construed as default by the Vendor/Promoter and ALLOTTEE/PURCHASER shall not be entitled to any compensation for such delays.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                 <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">b)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Vendor[s]/Promoter[s], soon after the Schedule “C” is ready<strong>[except the finishing works such as final coat of paint, electrification/wiring, fixation of CP/Sanitary fixing and common amenities etc.,]</strong>  shall intimate the Allottee/Purchaser post which, with prior appointment, the Allottee/Purchaser shall visit the Schedule “C” apartment and notify the snag points [construction defects] to the Vendor/Promoter so as to enable the Vendor/Promoter to fix the same before handing over of possession of Schedule “C” apartment to the Allottee[s] /Purchaser.  The total duration for fixing the same may vary from item to item based on the complexity of the snag/problem notified by the Allottee[s] /Purchaser.  However, the Allottee[s] /Purchaser understands that this shall be an ongoing affair which may consume considerable time based on various factors such as nature of complaint/snag, availability of man-power/material etc., and the shall  not be entitled to retain/hold the final due payable to the Vendor/Promoter on account of delay in fixing the snag points.  
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                 <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">c)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/Purchaser shall be entitled for possession of the Schedule “C” property after he/she makes the final payment as set out in this Agreement and all other dues arising out of any increase in developmental charges, extra works etc., The Allottee/Purchaser shall duly make an application to the VENDOR/PROMOTER for issuance of No Due Certificate and other document as specified in clause 3(j) supra.  The possession of Schedule “C” mentioned property shall be delivered to the Allottee/Purchaser within 15 days from the date of issuance of No Due Certificate. The Vendor/Promoter shall not be liable in any manner whatsoever, for failure of the Allottee/Purchaser to take over possession of the Apartment.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                 <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">d)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/Purchaser shall take possession of the Apartment from the Vendor/Promoter by executing necessary Affidavits, indemnities, undertakings and such other documentation as prescribed by the Vendor/Promoter, and the Vendor/Promoter shall give possession of the Apartment to the Allottee/Purchaser. In case the Allottee/Purchaser fails to take possession within the time provided in clause 4(b), such Allottee shall continue to be liable to pay maintenance charges as applicable.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                 <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">e)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Vendor/Promoter shall hand over possession of the Apartment to the Allottee/Purchaser as committed subject to receipt of the entire consideration including the other payments and subject to the condition set out in clause 3(j) supra. It is made abundantly clear that the obligation of the Vendor/Promoter to hand over the Apartment to the Allottee/Purchaser does not arise until the Vendor/Promoter receives the entire payment/s as mentioned in Schedule “D” and issue No Due Certificate.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                 <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">f)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/Purchaser shall not permit any agent/workers to carry out any work in the Apartment, until possession is handed over to the Allottee.  
                    </td>
                </tr>
            </table>
            <p style="padding-top:20px; text-align:justify;">
                5.<span style="padding-left: 30px"><strong><u>BREACH OF TERMS AND ITS REMEDY:</u></strong></span>
            </p>
            <p style="padding-left:30px; text-align:justify;">
                <strong>(a)</strong>  <span style="padding-left: 20px"><strong>ALLOTTEE’S COVENANT: </strong></span>
            </p>
            <table>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">1.</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        In the event of the Allottee/Purchaser failing to pay the aforesaid sums, in the manner provided in Schedule-D” or cancel/withdraw from the Project except for the default of the Vendor/Promoter, then the Vendor/Promoter, at their discretion after due notice of 15 days to the Allottee/Purchaser, is entitled to cancel this Agreement and re-allot the Apartment, to another party and the Allottee/Purchaser shall thereafter have no right, interest or claim over the Apartment. Consequent to such termination and re-allotment of the apartment to the prospective purchaser, subject to deduction of the booking amount, the Vendor/Promoter shall refund the monies collected from the Allottee/Purchaser within 15 days of such re-allotment without interest, simultaneous to the Allottee/Purchaser executing necessary cancellation and registration of the Agreement and/or sale deed by the Allottee/Purchaser. It is clarified that the Allottee shall not be entitled to claim refund till the Apartment is re-allotted/sold to a prospective purchaser and execution of cancellation of the Agreement/s executed in favour of the Allottee/Purchaser. The period of 15 days provided for refund shall commence only from the date of re-allotment or sale of the Apartment to a prospective purchaser, as the case may be and/or execution of cancellation agreements, whichever is later.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">2.</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/Purchaser hereby agrees that the assignment of the Allottee’s/Purchaser right under this agreement to any third party is subject to the prior written permission of the Vendor/Promoter and further agrees to pay to the Vendor/Promoter an Assignment fee of 5% of Construction Cost (‘Assignment Fee’).    
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">3.</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Parties hereby confirm that this Agreement and the Agreement for Sale of even date entered into by the Allottee/Purchaser shall co-exist or co-terminate and that breach either will result in the breach of the other also.     
                    </td>
                </tr>
            </table>
            <p style="padding-left:30px; text-align:justify;">
                <strong>(b)</strong>  <span style="padding-left: 20px"><strong>VENDOR/PROMOTER’S COVENANT: </strong></span>
            </p>
            <p style="padding-left:30px; text-align:justify; margin-top:-10px">
                Subject to the Force Majeure clause, the Vendor/Promoter shall be considered to be on default, in the following events:
                
            </p>
            <table>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">1.</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        Vendor/Promoter fails to provide ready to move in possession of the Apartment to the Allottee/Purchaser within the time period specified. For the purpose of this clause, 'ready to move in possession' shall mean that the apartment shall be in a habitable condition which is complete in all respects;
                        
                    </td> </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">2.</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        Discontinuance of the Vendor/Promoter’s business as a developer on account of suspension or revocation of his registration under the provisions of the RERA Act or the rules or regulations made there under;
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">3.</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        In case of Default by Vendor/Promoter under the conditions listed above, Allottee/Purchaser is entitled to the following:  
                    </td>
                </tr>
            </table>
            
            <table>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top; padding-left:30px">(i)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify; padding-left:30px;">
                        Stop making further payments to Vendor/Promoter as demanded by the Vendor/Promoter. If the Allottee/Purchaser stops making payments, the Promoter shall correct the situation by completing the construction milestones and only thereafter the Allottee/Purchaser be required to make the next payment without any penal interest; or
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                 <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top; padding-left:30px">(ii)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify; padding-left:30px;"> 
                        The Allottee/Purchaser shall have the option of terminating the Agreement in which case the Vendor/Promoter shall be liable to refund the entire money paid by the Allottee/Purchaser under any head whatsoever towards the purchase of the Apartment, along with interest at the rate specified in the Rules within 30 days of receiving the termination notice, simultaneous to the execution of cancellation agreement and registration thereof, if required.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                 <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top; padding-left:30px">(iii)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify; padding-left:30px;"> 
                        Provided that where an Allottee/Purchaser does not intend to withdraw from the project or terminate the Agreement, he/she shall be paid, by the Vendor/promoter, interest at the rate specified in the Rules, for every month of delay till the handing over of the possession of the Apartment.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
            </table>
            <p style="padding-top:20px; text-align:justify; margin-top:-5px">
                6.<span style="padding-left: 30px"><strong><u>MAINTENANCE OF COMMON AREAS AND AMENITIES IN THE PROJECT:</u></strong></span>
            </p>
            <table>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">a)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/Purchaser shall become a member of the Association of Owners in the project and subject himself or herself to the Rules and By-laws framed therefore and use the Apartment only for residential purpose and consistent with the rights of other owners and occupiers of other Apartments and use its drains, sewages, water supplies, power connection and other common amenities with care and diligence.   
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">b)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/Purchaser shall bear the expenses along with other Apartment owners, for the maintenance and repairs of sewage drains, water and power supplies, white washing, maintenance of common space and other common area and amenities etc. The Allottee/Purchaser agrees and shall pay the maintenance charges as per the scope mentioned in Annexure – 2 herein for the amenities/common area as fixed by the Vendor/Promoter, Maintenance Agency or the Association, as the case may be.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">c)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        In the event of the maintenance of the common areas and amenities is by a Third Party Maintenance Agency, the Allottee/Purchaser, along with the  owners of the other Apartments,  agree to execute an independent maintenance agreement with such maintenance agency as per the Scope of Maintenance as mentioned in Annexure -2 herein. The rights, duties and obligation of maintenance of the Common Areas and amenities provided   in   the   Project   may   be   captured   in   the   said   maintenance   agreement (‘Maintenance Agreement’).
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">d)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Vendor/Promoter shall provide essential maintenance services to common areas/amenities/ facilities those are pertaining to the entire project, from the date of completion of the Project for a period 36  months @ Rs.3.5/- per sq.ft. per month plus applicable GST  by themselves or through any other agency appointed by the Vendor/Promoter.  The scope of maintenance is more clearly set out in the Annexure 2 hereto. It is further agreed by the allottee that the promoter shall commence the maintenance once the occupational amenities are ready irrespective of the fact that whether the allotte occupies the apartment or not .It is further agreed and accepted by the Allottee/Purchaser that, until the VENDOR/PROMOTER sells 85% of the project, the maintenance shall automatically renewed and extended for another period of  36 months from the date of expiration of initial 36 months as said above. In such an event, the Allottee/Purchaser shall pay the maintenance charges for the extended period with an escalation of 10% p.a from the existing cost. The Allottee/Purchaser undertakes to pay the maintenance charges by way of 12 equated quarterly installments payable at the beginning of the every quarter, so as to enable the Vendor/Promoter to carry out the maintenance without any demur. In the event of failure thereof, the Vendor/Promoter shall be entitled to debit the Corpus fund paid by the respective Allottee[s] /Purchaser who is at default.    It is clarified that the right of maintenance shall be vested with the Vendor/Promoter until the Vendor/Promoter sells 85% of its stake in the entire project.  It is further clarified that if Association desires to take over the maintenance before attaining sales of 85% of entire project as stated above, the same shall be handed over to the Association on a specific condition that the Vendor/Promoter shall not be liable to contribute any maintenance charges for the unsold inventory.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">e)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        Any expenditure towards providing additional amenities/specifications over and above the specifications detailed out in Annexure 1 &amp; 2 shall be met out by the Vendor/Promoter from and out of the Corpus Fund and the Allottee/Purchaser /Association may keep informed about the same through proper means of communication.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">f)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        Notwithstanding the amount paid by the Allottee[s] /Purchaser towards maintenance &amp; Corpus fund as set out above, it is hereby made clear to the Allottee[s] /Purchaser that the cost involved in creating IT infrastructure, either Hardware(Computers, keyboards, etc.,) or Software (ADDA etc.,) towards maintaining the day-to-day operations relating to facility management for the Society/Association, shall be paid by the Purchaser/Allottee separately. However, the Vendor/Promoter shall co-ordinate to provide such facilities in consultation with the Association. 
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">g)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The capital expenditure spent of the Corpus Fund shall be replenished by raising pro-rate demand and collection from each Allottee/Purchaser, if the Allottee/Purchaser defaults in making the proportionate Corpus Fund the Vendor/Promoter shall be entitled to collect the prescribed interest for the due payments, or the Vendor/Promoter is entitled to deduct the same from and out of the Corpus Fund.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">h)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/Purchaser along with the other Allottees/Purchasers of the Project shall ensure that the Owners Welfare Association is formed as per the provisions of the Tamil Nadu Apartment Ownership Act, 2022 (‘Owners Association’). The Vendor/Promoter shall render its co-operation and facilitate in formation of the Owners Association.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">i)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        It is agreed by the Allottee/Purchaser herein that only after the VENDOR/PROMOTER attains sale of 85% stake in the entire project as envisaged in clause 6(d) supra, the Flat Owners  Association shall be entitled take over the maintenance and the Allottee/Purchaser shall continue to pay the all costs, charges, expenses, relating to the management, maintenance and up keep of common areas and common facilities/amenities including but not limited to STP/ETP, Lifts, Motors, pumps, etc., within the Project on pro-rata basis or in another manner as deem fit by the Association. The Vendor/Promoter shall not be liable for any shortcomings or deficiency thereof, in any manner whatsoever. However, the Vendor/Promoter shall contribute 20% of actual maintenance charges towards unsold inventory.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">j)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        It  is  specifically  agreed  by  the  Allottee/Purchaser  that  the  Allottee/Purchaser  shall  pay  their  pro-rata maintenance charges for the common areas, common amenities / facilities in the Project in time and without any delay and in the event of the Allottee’s/Purchaser’s inability to pay the maintenance charges or any default or delay in payment of maintenance charges and deposits if any,  the Allottee/Purchaser may be deprived  of his /her /its /their rights to enjoy the common facilities and amenities. In addition to that, such defaults will be displayed in the notice board within the Project.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
            </table>
            <p style="padding-top:20px; text-align:justify;">
                7.<span style="padding-left: 30px"><strong><u>SANCTIONS AND APPROVALS:</u></strong></span>
            </p>
            <table>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(a)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The statutory approvals, including State and Central Government approvals/permissions including amendments/modifications/ alterations, its departments, local bodies, authorities, CMDA, TNEB, Corporation of Chennai, and all other concerned authorities, may mandate the Vendor/Promoter to hand over certain percentage of land to the statutory authorities concerned, as a condition for granting approval.  The Vendor/promoter shall have absolute discretion to vary/revise the internal plan from the presently approved plan by the competent authorities based on customer’s requirement with respect to individual flats in any/all blocks to satisfy the needs of the customer. The Vendor/Promoter shall have absolute discretion to determine and identify the portion of the land to be handed over for complying with the terms and conditions of statutory approvals.   
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(b)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Vendor/Promoter hereby covenants that the Project shall be constructed as per the approved building plan.  
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(c)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/Purchaser is aware that the present plans sanctioned by the competent authority is valid for specific term, the Vendor/promoter shall be responsible to get the approvals duly renewed, the Allottee/Purchaser hereby give their specific consent and empower the Vendor/promoter to file necessary renewal application with the appropriate authority and to comply with any statutory requirement for such renewal.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(d)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/s/Purchaser hereby further and specifically consents/agrees that the VENDOR/PROMOTER, during the construction of the project/any phase, shall be absolutely entitled to apply for revision of the existing approved plan in order to accommodate any new rule/regulation introduced by CMDA/DTCP/Fire Department/TNEB and other Competent Authorities <strong>[OR]</strong> in order to achieve more FSI, increase/decrease the size of the dwelling units, increase the number car parking, combining/amalgamating two or more dwelling units or to develop any additional phase by amalgamating adjacent properties to the property more fully described in the Schedule B hereunder which are permissible within the developments control rules or and carryout the same. Further, the VENDOR/PROMOTER shall, on behalf of the Allottee/Purchaser, be fully authorized to sign all forms, applications, declarations, undertaking or any other document in this regard.  This clause shall be treated as a Power of Attorney entrusted upon the VENDOR/PROMOTER / No objection Letter issued to the VENDOR/PROMOTER in this regard.    The Allottee[s] /Purchaser undertake that’s he/she shall not object/create any hindrance for such revision for any reason whatsoever.  The Allottee[s] /Purchaser further understand that such hindrance may delay the approval process and delivery of possession, for which the Vendor/Promoter shall not be held responsible.  
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                
            </table>
            <p style="padding-top:20px; text-align:justify;">
                <strong> 8.</strong> <span style="padding-left: 30px"><strong><u>DEFECTS LIABILITY:</u></strong></span>
            </p>
            <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;"></td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                The Vendor/Promoter shall rectify any structural defects with respect to the Apartment (normal wear and tear is exempted), which shall not be as the result of any commission or omission of the Allottee/Purchaser, any damages caused due to the acts of god or natural calamities or fire accidents, any willful or accidental damages caused, any damages caused due to tampering by the Allottee/Purchaser, any product that has been installed by the Vendor/Promoter brought to the notice of the Vendor/Promoter within 5 years from the date of intimating the readiness to handover of the Apartment and thereafter no claim shall be entertained against the Vendor/Promoter in respect of any alleged defective work in the Apartment and/or Project under any circumstances. The above liability of the Vendor/Promoter shall be restricted only to rectify /repair the above defects and any consequential damages will not be covered under this Agreement. Structural defects shall not include plastering hairline crack. Third party warranty on products shall be governed by the terms and conditions provided by the manufacturer of the respective products.
                </td>
            </tr>
            <p style="padding-top:20px; text-align:justify;">
                <strong> 9.</strong><span style="padding-left: 30px"><strong><u> SEWAGE TREATEMENT PLANT / LIFT / DIESEL GENERATOR (MEP)</u></strong></span>
            </p>
            <table>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">a)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Vendor/Promoter, as part of the specification/common amenities, shall provide a Sewage/Effluent Treatment of required capacity in order to manage the drainage/sewage in the project and treat the sewage water generated thereof.  The location of STP shall be as per the choice of the Vendor/Promoter. The Allottee[s]/Purchaser hereby undoubtedly understands that the responsibility of the Vendor/Promoter shall be ended on the date of erection of the plant in all respects.  The commissioning of STP shall be done and shall become operational only if the occupancy reaches 50% of the total no. of apartments in the project / phase.  The Association shall take over possession of the STP unit in all respects maximum within 30 days from the date of commissioning.  It is further made clear that notwithstanding the maintenance charges paid by the Allottee[s]/Purchaser, the Association shall alone be responsible towards the cost of operation &amp; maintenance of STP including electricity charges / AMC charges etc., howsoever arising on account of maintenance of STP.  The Vendor/Promoter, till the STP is made operational, shall facilitate the removal of sewage through tanker lorries / or by any other means and debit the cost to the corpus fund account. However, the Vendor/Promoter shall ensure that the cost incurred in disposal of sewage shall not exceed the day-to-day operational cost of STP unit which the Association would incur otherwise, if the STP is operational.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                    
                
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">b)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Vendor/Promoter shall provide one or more Diesel Generators with required capacity in order to give power back up to the minimum essential points inside the apartment and in the common areas as the case may be as per the specification mentioned in this Agreement. The location of DGs shall be as per the choice of the Vendor/Promoter. The Allottee[s]/Purchaser hereby undoubtedly understand that the responsibility of the Vendor/Promoter shall be ended on the date of erection of DG in all respects.  The procurement &amp; installation of DGs shall happen progressively based on the occupancy and electricity load to be consumed therein the project / phase.  The Association shall take over possession of the DGs as and when it is installed. It is further made clear that notwithstanding the maintenance charges paid by the Allotte[e]/Purchaser the Association shall alone be responsible towards the cost of operation &amp; maintenance of DGs including AMC charges, Fuel consumption charges etc.,  and hence, the Vendor/Promoter shall debit such cost to the Corpus Fund account. 
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">c)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Vendor/Promoter shall provide one or more passenger/service lifts in the block/core as the case may be as per the specification mentioned in this Agreement. The Allottee[s]/Purchaser hereby undoubtedly understand that the commissioning of Lifts shall happen progressively based on the occupancy and usage in the respective Blocks. It is further made clear that notwithstanding the maintenance charges paid by the Allottee /Purchaser, the Association shall alone be responsible towards the cost of operation &amp; maintenance of Lifts including AMC charges and hence, the Vendor/Promoter shall debit such cost to the corpus fund account.   
                    </td>
                </tr>
            </table>
            <p style="padding-top:20px; text-align:justify;">
                <strong> 10.</strong><span style="padding-left: 30px"><strong><u>INFRASTRUCTURE FOR / FIRE FIGHTING SYSTEM </u></strong></span>
            </p>
            <p style="text-align:justify; font-size:14px">
                The Vendor/Promoter has provided Fire Fighting system in the project as per approval firefighting norms.  The Vendor/Promoter, after erection of Fire Fighting system, shall make it operational and demonstrate the workability only before the Competent Authorities before obtaining the NOCs.  The Association representatives, if desired, can be present during such demonstration. The repair/maintenance cost shall be that of the Association and shall be debited to the Corpus Fund.  In the event of any additional Demonstration is required by the Association, the same shall be facilitated only on chargeable basis.
                
            </p>
            <p style="padding-top:20px; text-align:justify;">
                <strong> 11.</strong><span style="padding-left: 30px"><strong><u>LOANS AND FINANCIAL ASSISTANCES:</u></strong></span>
            </p>
            <table>
                
                
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(a)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The original Sale Deed relating to the SCHEDULE “C” PROPERTY will be under the custody of the Vendor/Promoter till such time all / last payment including cost of construction and extra amenities are paid / settled by the Allottee/Purchaser to the Vendor/Promoter. However, if the Allottee/Purchaser prefers/s to avail loan, the original Sale Deed in respect of SCHEDULE “C” PROPERTY will be released directly to the mortgagee  /  Banks  /  Financial  Institutions,  after  obtaining  a  commitment  letter  from  the mortgagee / banks / financial institutions. 
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                
<div style="padding-top:20px"></div>                
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(b)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Vendor/Promoter undertakes to furnish one set of photocopies of title deeds pertaining to the SCHEDULE “B” PROPERTY to the Allottee/Purchaser. In the event of foreclosure of the loan by the Allottee/Purchaser prior to handing over the SCHEDULE “C” PROPERTY by the Vendor/Promoter to the Allottee/Purchaser, the Allottee/Purchaser shall hand over the original Sale Deed to the Vendor/Promoter and the Vendor/Promoter will have the custody of the documents till such time all / last payment including cost of construction and extra amenities are paid / settled by the Allottee/Purchaser to the Vendor/Promoter.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(c)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        All the payments to be paid under this Agreement by the Allottee/Purchaser to the Vendor/Promoter, apart from the loan amount, shall be paid directly by the Allottee/Purchaser to the Vendor/Promoter;
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(d)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        All the loan amount/s, availed by the Allottee/Purchaser, shall be directly disbursed / released by the bank / financial institution to the Vendor/Promoter and the same shall be treated as payments made on behalf of the Allottee/Purchaser;
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(e)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        Notwithstanding whether the loan is obtained or not, the Allottee/Purchaser shall still be liable to pay to the Vendor/Promoter on the due dates the relevant installments and all other sums due under this Agreement and in the event, if there is any delay and or default is made in payment of such amount/s, the Allottee/Purchaser shall be liable for the consequences including payment of delayed payment charges on the outstanding payment as provided in this agreement.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
            </table>
            <p style="padding-top:20px; text-align:justify;">
                <strong> 12.</strong><span style="padding-left: 30px"><strong><u> RIGHTS AND DUTIES OF THE ALLOTTEE:</u></strong></span>
            </p>
            <table>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(a)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        While the Allottee/Purchaser would have absolute and exclusive ownership possession/enjoyment of the Apartment, after handing over, the Allottee’s/Purchaser’s right, title and interest in the common areas shall be enjoyed in concurrence with other owners/residents of other apartments in the Project, who would be equally entitled to the common amenities/facilities/easements available in the Project, all costs of repairs/maintenance of which common enjoyments shall be shared by all the owners, including the Allottee/Purchaser as per the articles/regulations/bye-laws of the Association to be formed by all the apartment owners in the Project;
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(b)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        It is abundantly made clear that all the service lines, ducts, water courses and other facilities passing through the Said Land shall be treated as common to all the owners, which shall be maintained by the Association. The owners of the apartments shall not object to the common services passing through their respective apartments and allow the service persons to do the maintenance services in the areas through which the services are passing through;
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(c)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/Purchaser shall adhere to the maintenance and usage guidelines provided by the Association to maintain harmonious community living and ensure that rights and enjoyment of other apartment owners are not affected;
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(d)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/Purchaser covenants not to make any alteration in the structure of the Apartment, which may affect directly or indirectly, the structural safety &amp; stability and the aesthetic elevation of the building complex; In the event of the structural or other defect arising in the construction due to any alteration and/or interior work carried out by the Allottee, the Vendor/Promoter shall not be responsible for the same or  its rectification;
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(e)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/Purchaser or their tenants(Occupants)and/or Association shall not, at any time, encroach and carry on in the common areas or within the SCHEDULE “B” PROPERTY, any commercial trade or business or use it for  storage of anything  which is offensive in nature, hazardous or inflammable or is likely to be a nuisance or danger or diminish the value or the utility of the other portions of the building in the Project in occupation of the owners of other apartments or their successors in title and further shall not do or commit any activity which is unlawful and anti– social;
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;"></td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/Purchaser shall either in his/her/its/their individual capacity or as a member of the Association Society, after its formation, come to an understanding with the other owners of the apartment shall operate and maintain all the essential amenities like STP, Genset, elevator, Rainwater harvesting etc., either individually or through the Association whenever required and in good running condition. It is the responsibility of the Allottee/Purchaser and or the Association to ensure proper assistance to the government officials concerned during periodical inspection. The Allottee/Purchaser shall not either in his/her/its/their individual capacity or as a member of the Association, after its formation, come to an understanding with the other owners of the apartment to utilize the common areas for commercial purposes or for earning income from outsiders;
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(f)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/Purchaser agrees to sign from time to time all papers and documents and to do all things as the Promoter may require, for the effective completion of the construction and in matters connected with obtaining, erecting and providing the infrastructural facilities like water, sewerage, electricity, etc.;
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
               <tr>
    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top; padding-top:20px;">(g)</td>
    <td width="95%" style="text-align:left; padding-top:20px;">
        The Allottee/Purchaser shall not encroach upon the common areas;  
    </td>
</tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(h)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/Purchaser shall not decorate the exterior of the proposed buildings in the Project otherwise than in a manner agreed to by the majority of the apartment owners with the prior permission of the Association; However, the Allottee/Purchaser, for a period of three years from the date of handing over possession of Schedule C property, shall not be authorized to cover the balcony by erecting/putting up grill or any other material.  In the event of the Allottee/Purchaser doing so, the VENDOR/PROMOTER shall be entitled to remove the same by itself or through any third party agency at the cost of the Allottee/Purchaser.  In case of non-payment of such cost within 30 days from the date of its occurrence, the VENDOR/PROMOTER is also entitled to deduct the same from the Corpus fund paid by respective Allottees/Purchasers.  In such an event, the Promoter shall have a right to retain or forfeit the Corpus fund paid by the respective Allottees/Purchasers till the rectification is carried out and cost for the same is recovered in full.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(i)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/Purchaser shall not put up any temporary or permanent structure anywhere in the Project nor change the elevation of the proposed buildings; In the event of the Allottee/Purchaser doing so, the VENDOR/PROMOTER shall be entitled to remove the same by itself or through any third party agency at the cost of the Allottee/Purchaser.   
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(j)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/Purchaser shall not make any alterations in the structural feature of the proposed building like R.C.C.Flooring, Roofing, columns and external walls during \after completion, including the parking space allotted;
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(k)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/Purchaser shall use the Apartment only for residential purposes and not to use for any other purposes and for business prohibited by law; 
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(l)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/Purchaser shall not cause any nuisance to the other occupants of proposed apartments in the Project;
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(m)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/Purchaser shall have no right to hinder the progress of construction of the residential apartment buildings in the Project or any part thereof under any circumstances whatsoever, and at whatever stage of construction; It is further clarified to the Allottee/Purchaser that, in order to ensure smooth work flow and quality of work, he/she shall be liable to obtain prior appointment from the Vendor/Promoter before visiting the project site for inspection of construction progress and/or for any other purposes.  The Vendor/Promoter or their representative/staff are not liable to meet/attend the Allottee[s] /Purchaser or their representatives, in case of no prior appointment.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(n)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/Purchaser shall give all necessary support, assistance to the other apartment owners/Association. The supporting common walls and roofs and all common areas of the buildings in the Project shall be maintained and repaired in common by all the owners of the apartments in the Project;  
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(o)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/Purchaser shall park their cars/vehicles only at the specific car parking space allotted to the Allottee/Purchaser  and not at any other place around the building and shall use the Car Parking space only for parking their vehicles and shall not use the parking space for other purposes including storage of materials;
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(p)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Allottee/Purchaser or the Association of Owners shall not in any way obstruct or interfere with the construction and related activity that may be on going and  required to complete the project, particularly the balances phases, where the project is being developed in phases. In this regard the Allottee/Purchaser and/or the Association shall not interfere or obstruct the movement of men, material, etc., as may require for the construction and completion of the Project. 
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(q)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Promoter is, until the entire project is fully sold and handed over or completion of maintenance tenure whichever is later, entitled to take photographs / video of the project site or any part thereof during day / night for the purpose of their marketing activity and to conduct any sale/marketing event/mela etc., by itself or by engaging any other event management/marketing/third party agency.  The Allottee/Purchaser or the Flat Owner’s Association shall not be authorized to object to the same.  However, such activity shall be done/carried out without causing any hindrance/nuisance to the residents. The Allottee/Purchaser undertakes/consents that the bye-law/objective of the Association shall be framed only in consonance with various covenants the Allottee/Purchaser have agreed herein.  
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(r)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        It is unambiguously agreed by the Allottee[s] /Purchaser that any dispute/difference of opinion which may arise between the Allottee[s]/Association and Vendor/Promoter in respect of maintenance, construction quality etc., and the same shall be sorted out/settled only by due process of law by way of the guideline set out in the clause 31 [Dispute Resolution].  It further agreed by the Allottee(s) /Purchaser(s) that, apart from settling the dispute/difference of opinion in the manner stated in clause 31 below, the Allottee(s) /Purchaser(s) or the Association shall not create any kind hindrance to the marketing activities / pending works in unsold apartments carried out by the Vendor/Promoter by (i) restraining the entry/exit of the staff / labourers / prospective customers to the project site (ii) display banners / hoardings with negative phrases or (iii) do any other activity which may hamper the business of the Vendor/Promoter.  Despite this undertaking, if the Allottee/Purchaser in his/her individual capacity or the Association involves in such activities including but not limited to those which are mentioned above, the Vendor/Promoter shall be entitled to deduct 2% of Corpus Fund per day towards liquidated damages.  If the entire corpus fund is exhausted by way of the aforesaid adjustments, even after which the Association continues to create hindrance to the marketability of the project, the Vendor/Promoter shall have right to deduct / recover these losses from the maintenance cost paid by the Allottee/Purchaser.  The Allottee[s] /Purchaser[s] understand that in such an event, the maintenance tenure shall be automatically stand reduced in proportion to the amount deducted as mentioned above.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(s)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        It is specifically agreed by the Allottee/Purchaser that the Allottee/Purchaser shall bear all statutory charges from the date of intimating the readiness of the Apartment for handover by the Vendor/Promoter.
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
            </table>
            <p style="padding-top:20px; text-align:justify;">
                <strong> 13.</strong><span style="padding-left: 30px"><strong><u>RIGHTS AND DUTIES OF VENDOR/PROMOTER:</u></strong></span>
            </p>
            <table>
                
                
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(a)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Promoter undertakes to develop the Project with good workmanship using standard materials, through its own labour, materials, tools, machineries and other equipment for the purpose of construction,  or by  appointing  contractors  / sub – contractors,  engineers and supervisors at their choice and to take steps to complete the SCHEDULE“C” PROPERTY within the time stipulated for completion of the same;
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(b)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Vendor/Promoter shall be responsible and liable to pay the land tax in respect of the said Land up to the date of execution and registration of Sale Deed in respect of SCHEDULE-C PROPERTY or delivery of possession of the SCHEDULE-C PROPERTY to the Allottee/Purchaser, whichever is earlier. From the date of intimating the readiness to hand over possession, the Allottee/Purchaser is solely responsible and liable for property tax and other relevant taxes/charges and duties to the respective authorities with respect to the SCHEDULE C PROPERTY;
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(c)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                        The Vendor/Promoter will provide only electrical points.  The cost  of  all  electrical  fixtures and consumables like bulbs, fans, fittings etc., will be borne by the Allottee/Purchaser;
                        
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <div style="padding-top:20px"></div>
                <tr >
                    <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">(d)</td>
                    <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
