            <p style="padding-top:20px; text-align:justify;">
                <strong> 30.</strong><span style="padding-left: 30px"><strong><u>GOVERNING LAW:</u></strong></span>
            </p>
            <tr >
                <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;"></td>
                <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                    That the rights and obligations of the parties under or arising out of this Agreement shall be construed and enforced in accordance with the laws of India for the time being in force.
                    
                </td>
            </tr>
            <p style="padding-top:20px; text-align:justify;">
                <strong> 31.</strong><span style="padding-left: 30px"><strong><u>OTHER MATTERS:</u></strong></span>
            </p>
            
            <tr >
                <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">a)</td>
                <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                    THE VENDOR/PROMOTER shall pass on the warranty and guarantee offered by the manufacturers of all the equipment’s and machinery used in the project. On expiry of the warranty period, the association should get into maintenance contract with the manufactures at their own cost. No extension of warranty shall be provided by the VENDOR/PROMOTER unless the association gets into a separate contract with the VENDOR/PROMOTER for the same.
                    
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr >
                <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">b)</td>
                <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                    The Vendor/Promoter shall be entitled to allot Open/Covered/Stack Car Parking as the case may be for the use of the Allottee/Purchaser agreed that, as the Allottees/Purchasers requires the car park for his / her exclusive use. The Vendor/Promoter is allotting the same by assigning a number or by earmarking the area in the site without collecting any cost/charges towards the same.  It is further agreed that the rights to use the exclusive car park would run co-terminus with the rights of ownership of the relevant apartment.  It is further agreed that depending on the availability of such spaces, the Vendor/Promoter would be entitled to allot car parking slots on "first cum first serve" basis.  The Allottee/Purchaser further covenants and undertakes that he/she shall use the car parking space, if any allotted  to him/her as car parking space only and shall not convert it to any other use nor shall put up or construct any wall or structure thereon. Further, the approving authorities viz. CMDA/DTCP/MLPA/CLPA or local body shall have charge over such parking spaces and at any point of time if there are any unauthorized conversion into other uses, the building is liable for enforcement action by the Local Planning Authority or the Regional Deputy Director of DTCP or designated agency as provisions of the Tamil Nadu Town Country Planning Act. Accordingly, the  Allottee/Purchaser shall be eligible to park their cars in the space exclusively earmarked and more clearly described in the schedule ‘C’ hereunder. The parking of vehicles in the common area other than the areas marked as reserved car parks is also prohibited.   The Allottee/Purchaser understands that the Open/stack Reserved Car Parking spaces are allocated in the setback area owing to the fact that the provision of car parking in covered spaces for all the apartment is not practically possible.  It is further understood by the Allottee(s), apart from covered parking, the stack/open reserved parking are provided/earmarked in the setback area only for their convenience and to ensure that maximum flat owners are provided with the parking facility so as to maintain the harmony amongst all residents.  All the decision relating car parking allotment shall solely be vested with the Developer 
                    
                    and the same shall not be questioned/disputed either by the Allottee(s) /Purchaser individually or by the resident welfare association, collectively.  The Allottee(s) /Purchaser(s) unequivocally agree and undertake not to object the allotment of such open reserved /stack parking under any circumstances.  Despite the elaborate clarification/condition, in case of any objection/dispute from any resident/Allottee/buyer, the Allottee/Purchaser agrees resolve such dispute/objection through the resident welfare association without referring such disputes/objections to the Builder/Promoter. 
                    
                </td>
            </tr>
            
            <tr >
                <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">c)</td>
                <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                    The ALLOTTEE/PURCHASER understands that the VENDOR/PROMOTER shall be entitled to allot private open terrace/private garden/service area as the case may be for the use of the other Allottee[s] /Purchaser for their exclusive use. It is further agreed that the rights to use such space would run co-terminus with the rights of ownership of the relevant apartment. It is further agreed that the respective Allottee[s/Purchaser] to whom such private terrace/private garden/service area are allotted shall have exclusive usage right over the same the other Allottee[s] /Purchaser shall have no right/jurisdiction to object the same. However, the Allottee[s] undertakes not to put up any permanent / temporary structure to cover such Pvt. Terrace/Garden. In the event of the Allottee[s] /Purchaser doing so, the VENDOR/PROMOTER shall be entitled to remove the same by itself or through any third party agency at the cost of the Allottee/Purchaser.
                    
                </td>
            </tr>
            
            <tr >
                <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">d)</td>
                <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                    The Allottee/Purchaser has been fully appraised of the fact that an extent of 426.00 Sq.mt or 4585.46 Sq.ft. has been specifically earmarked towards establishment of a Substation by the TANGEDCO / Tamil Nadu Electricity Board (TNEB), as per the prevailing norms. The Allottee/Purchaser understands that the Undivided Share pertaining to the Schedule C mentioned apartment has been calculated only after deducting the said land portion earmarked for Sub-station.  The Allottee/Purchaser further undertakes not to object the gifting of the said portion of the land by the Vendor/Promoter, as and when required by TANGEDCO.  The Allottee/Purchaser further undertakes to not create any obstruction/disturbance in future when the officials/workmen of TANGEDCO/TNEB access the said land for operation and maintenance.  The Allottee/Purchaser further understands that the TANGEDCO shall be at its liberty to provide the electric load to any of the adjacent properties in the vicinity as they deem fit.  In such an event, the Promoter takes no responsibility whatsoever for the same. 
                    
                </td>
            </tr>
            
            <tr >
                <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">e)</td>
                <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                    The Vendor/Promoter shall provide the recreational facilities such as Club house with Gym, aerobics etc., at their own cost in the as earmarked in the Approved plan. The Vendor/Promoter shall maintain the same by leasing the same or under their supervision having full control and authority till the entire project is completed and sold.  The decision of the Vendor/Promoter shall be final and binding in maintaining such recreational facilities. 
                    
                </td>
            </tr>
            
            <tr >
                <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">f)</td>
                <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                    The Allottee/Purchaser shall automatically become a member of all the recreational facilities provided in the building complex.  The Allottee shall pay the maintenance charges and recurring expenses for using such recreational facilities as may be fixed by the Vendor/Promoter or its authorized agency from time to time.
                    
                </td>
            </tr>
            
            <tr >
                <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">g)</td>
                <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                    The Vendor/Promoter shall be undisputedly entitled to lease/rent the unsold apartments owned by them in the project for the purpose of co-living spaces to bachelors/families/MNCs &amp; Corporate Companies for Guest House / any for other purposes which are legally permitted for residential use.  It is clarified that such co-living spaces can be managed either by the builder or through any third party duly authorized by the builder/ Vendor/promoter under any terms and conditions as deem fit by the Vendor/Promoter or its authorized agent. In such an event, the maintenance charges pertaining to those apartments shall be paid to the Resident Welfare Association which shall be on par with the charges collected from the other residents.  Save and except the maintenance charges, no other amount shall become payable to the Resident Welfare Association on any account whatsoever.  It is further clarified that the tenants/occupants of such apartments, which are demarcated/rented out for co-living purposes shall be entitled to use all the common areas/amenities.  The Association shall be entitled to collect separate charges as applicable for usage of club house / gym or any other facility which are running in the project on chargeable basis. However, such charges shall not exceed the charges applicable to the other flat owners.
                    
                </td>
            </tr>
            
            <tr >
                <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">h)</td>
                <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                    The Allottee[s] /Purchaser should pay a caution deposit of Rs.50,000/- if they need to do the interior work on their own in the flat such as (Tiling, painting, grill work, false ceiling, Modular work, etc.,). Once they complete the work the engineer appointed by the Vendor/Promoter will visit the common area if any damages has been done then corresponding amount will be deducted from the caution deposit and balance shall be refunded within 3 working days.
                    
                </td>
            </tr>
            
            <tr >
                <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">i)</td>
                <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                    The Allottee(s) agrees that the positioning of the transformer (if any), the Water sump/s, STP sump/s and units, generators (if any), cylinder storage room (if any) and drivers/watchman toilets shall be as specified by the concerned consultant/authority or the Vendor/Promoter. The Allottee(s/Purchaser(s) shall not be entitled to interfere in this matter. 
                    
                </td>
            </tr>
            
            <tr >
                <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">j)</td>
                <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
                    The Allottee/Purchaser acknowledges that the Vendor/Promoter will not provide or establish any water sources, such as wells or borewells within the project, as the groundwater at the site is not fit for domestic use and treating it for safe use is not feasible, as the cost of maintaining a water treatment/RO plant would be high.  The Purchaser, along with other co-owners or the Flat Owners’ Association, agrees to independently arrange for water supply by either creating a water source or purchasing water through tanker services at their own expenses.  Further, these costs are not included in the project’s maintenance scope set out in Annexure 2 hereof. Further, the Purchaser understands that the price of the Schedule 'C' apartment has been determined with this situation taken into consideration and proceeds with the purchase of the Schedule 'C' property with full knowledge of these facts.
                    
                </td>
            </tr>
            
            <tr >
                <td width="5%" style="text-align:justify; vertical-align:top;">k)</td>
                <td width="95%" style="text-align:justify;">
