            <p style="text-align:left;">
               <strong><u>GENERAL TERMS</u></strong> 
            </p>
            <ol style="text-align:left; margin-left:25px">
                  <li>Civil related complaints like leakage, electrical low voltage, wire loose connections and other inner flat works will not be the scope of the maintenance agency.</li>
                  <li>Awarding / Renewal of AMC Contracts for motors, Gensets, STP, Water level indicator &amp; lifts will not be the Scope of the Maintenance Agency and shall be in the scope of Residents / Association. However, necessary remainders and follow-ups will be initiated by the Party of the First Part.</li>
                  <li>Power backup to the common areas including lift can be given only during emergency and unexpected power shutdown. Providing power backup during scheduled power cuts does not come under the scope of the maintenance agency. Diesel consumption charges up to Rs.10,000 / month will be in the scope of the Maintenance Agency &amp; beyond that shall be in the scope of Residents / Association.</li>
                  <li>Purchase of water will not come under the scope of the maintenance agency.</li>
                  <li>Common electricity bill amount will be paid up to the limit of Rs.40,000 /month by the Maintenance Agency, beyond which the cost incurred shall be that of the Residents / Association.</li>
                  <li>The cost incurred in bailing out sewage water shall be that of the Association. However, all necessary assistance shall be provided by the maintenance agency.</li>
                  <li>The maintenance agency shall not be held responsible for any sewage blockage inside the flats.</li>
                  <li>Electrical/plumbing fittings/street light post/lamp will not be replaced by the maintenance agency. Any asset replacement or implementation has to be carried out by the Association.</li>
                  <li>Internal complaints (inside the flat) will not be under the scope of the maintenance agency.</li>
                  <li>Any seepage/leakage in the common area or the inner flat area will not be under the scope of the maintenance agency.</li>
